<style>
b {
  word-break: break-all;
  text-size-adjust: unset;
  }
.errorDetails {
    background-color: red;
    border-radius: 5px;
    margin: 5px;
}  
.card-container {
    background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);
    margin: auto;
    width: calc(95%);

    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
}
.form-group {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    flex-flow: column !important;
}
#checkout-form {
    position: relative;
    width: 400px;
    padding: 10px;
}

#checkout-form label {
    display: block;
    min-height: 25px;

    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 5px 0;
    padding: 0;
    color: red;
}

#card-number, #card-cvv, #card-expiry {
    background-color: #FFF;
    display: block;
    width: calc(90%);
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(200, 200, 200, 1);
    padding: 14px 60px 13px 20px;
    margin: auto;
    transition: all 100ms ease-out;
}

/* card images are added to card number */
#card-number {
    background-image: none;

    background-origin: content-box;
    background-position: calc(100% + 40px) center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: contain;
}

/* buttons */
.btn {
    vertical-align: top;
}

#pay-button {
    position: relative;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: #0c384f;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1);
    display: inline-block;
    transition: all 100ms ease-out;
    padding: 11px 25px;
    margin-left: 30px;
}

#pay-button:hover, #pay-button:active {
    background-color: rgba(69, 36, 89, 1);
}

#pay-button:active {
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 35px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}

#pay-button:disabled {
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1);
    border: 1px solid #0c384f;
    color: #0c384f;
}

/* feedback is displayed after tokenization */
#feedback {
    position: relative;
    left: 15px;
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: transparent;
    border: 0px solid rgba(200, 200, 200, 1);
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: all 100ms ease-out;
    padding: 11px;
}

#feedback.error {
    color: red;
    border: 1px solid;
}

#feedback.success {
    color: seagreen;
    border: 1px solid;
}
</style>

<script>
  var tax1Value;
  var tax2Value;
  var tax3Value;
  
  function GetURLParameter(sParam){
    arr=window.location.hash.split(sParam+"=");
    if (arr.length>0){
      return arr[1];
    }
    return null;
  }  
</script>

<script>
var termsInformation="";
var discounts;
function completeTableChange(pageReload){
  K('field[Family Member]').value("");
	$(K("form").find("#selectFamilyMemberMenu [class$='placeholder']")).html("Select...");  				
  K('field[Programs]').value("");
  K('field[tableMemberID]').value("");
  K('field[tableMemberName]').value("");
  K('field[tableProgram]').value("");
  K('field[tableFee]').value("");
  
  // Sort table
  viewerConfig.response.sort(function(a, b){return b.cost - a.cost});
  // Let calculate the discounts
  viewerConfig.response.forEach(function(item, index){
    if (index<=discounts.length-1){
      item.discount=discounts[index].discount;
      item.fee=((new Number(item.cost))*discounts[index].cost).toFixed(2);
    } else if (index>discounts.length-1 && discounts.length>0){
      item.discount=discounts[discounts.length-1].discount;
      item.fee=((new Number(item.cost))*discounts[discounts.length-1].cost).toFixed(2);
    } else {
    item.discount="0%";
    item.fee=((new Number(item.cost))).toFixed(2);
    }
  });
  debugger;
  // Set payment value
 
  if (pageReload===undefined) { // Not recalcuated if Prev Page reloaded
    var feeTotal=0;
    var subTotal=0;
    var total=0;
    viewerConfig.response.forEach(function(item, index){
      feeTotal=feeTotal+(new Number((new Number(item.fee)).toFixed(2)));
    });
    if (feeTotal===0) {
      K('field[Fee Total]').value("");
      K('field[TAX 1]').value("");
      K('field[TAX 2]').value("");
      K('field[TAX 3]').value("");
      K('field[I promise to pay equal FREQUENCY instalments of]').value("");
    } else {
      // Add taxes if configured
      if (tax1Value!==undefined && tax1Value!==null){
        var value=feeTotal*(new Number(tax1Value));
        value=new Number(value.toFixed(2));
        K('field[TAX 1]').value(value);
        subTotal=subTotal+value;
      }
      if (tax2Value!==undefined && tax2Value!==null){
        var value=feeTotal*(new Number(tax2Value));
        value=new Number(value.toFixed(2));
        K('field[TAX 2]').value(value);
        subTotal=subTotal+value;
      }
      if (tax3Value!==undefined && tax3Value!==null){
        var value=feeTotal*(new Number(tax3Value));
        value=new Number(value.toFixed(2));
        K('field[TAX 3]').value();
        subTotal=subTotal+value;
      }
      total=feeTotal+subTotal;
      K('field[I promise to pay equal FREQUENCY instalments of]').value(total.toFixed(2));
/*      if ((tax1Value!==undefined && tax1Value!==null) || (tax2Value!==undefined && tax2Value!==null) || (tax3Value!==undefined && tax3Value!==null)) {
	      K('field[Fee Total]').value(feeTotal.toFixed(2));        
      } */
	      K('field[Fee Total]').value(feeTotal.toFixed(2));              
    }
  }
  global.viewerConfig.renderer.type($('#memberTableDiv'),global.viewerConfig);

  $('#member-table tbody tr').on( 'click', function () {
    if ( $(this).hasClass('selected') ) {
      $(this).removeClass('selected');
    }
    else {
      $('#member-table').DataTable().$('tr.selected').removeClass('selected');
      $(this).addClass('selected');
    }
  } );  
  K('field[feesJSON]').value(JSON.stringify(viewerConfig.response));

  members=new Array();
  viewerConfig.response.forEach(function(item){
    members.push(item.id);
  });
  K('field[membersJSON]').value(JSON.stringify(members));  
}  
  
function memberProgramAdded(memberID, feeProgram) {
  found=false;

  viewerConfig.response.forEach(function(item){
      if (item.id===memberID && item.feeProgram===feeProgram) {
        found=true;
      }
  });  
  return found;
}
</script>
<script>
function enabledAddressEdit(){
  K('field[Address]').enable();
  K('field[Suburb]').enable();
  K('field[State]').enable();
  K('field[Postcode]').enable();
}
function geolocate() {
  if (navigator.geolocation) {
    navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(function(position) {
      var geolocation = {
        lat: position.coords.latitude,
        lng: position.coords.longitude
      };
      var circle = new google.maps.Circle(
          {center: geolocation, radius: position.coords.accuracy});
      autocomplete.setBounds(circle.getBounds());
    });
  }
}
function fillInAddress() {
  K("field[Address]").value("");

  // Get the place details from the autocomplete object.
  var place = autocomplete.getPlace();

debugger;
  // Get each component of the address from the place details,
  // and then fill-in the corresponding field on the form.
  for (var i = 0; i < place.address_components.length; i++) {
    var addressType = place.address_components[i].types[0];

    if (addressType==="street_number") {
    	K("field[Address]").value(place.address_components[i]["long_name"]);
    }
    if (addressType==="route") {
    	K("field[Address]").value(K("field[Address]").value()+" "+place.address_components[i]["long_name"]);
    }
    if (addressType==="locality") {
    	K("field[Suburb]").value(place.address_components[i]["long_name"]);
    }
    if (addressType==="administrative_area_level_1") {
    	K("field[State]").value(place.address_components[i]["short_name"]);
    }
    if (addressType==="postal_code") {
    	K("field[Postcode]").value(place.address_components[i]["short_name"]);
    }
/*    if (addressType==="country") {
    	K("field[Country]").value(place.address_components[i]["long_name"]);
    } */
  }
}  
function initAutocomplete() {
  debugger;
  if (document.getElementById('autocomplete')!==undefined) {
    // Create the autocomplete object, restricting the search predictions to
    // geographical location types.
    try {
      if (document.getElementById('autocomplete')!==null) {
	      autocomplete = new google.maps.places.Autocomplete(
          document.getElementById('autocomplete'), {types: ['geocode']});

  	    // Avoid paying for data that you don't need by restricting the set of
    	  // place fields that are returned to just the address components.
      	autocomplete.setFields(['address_component']);

      	// When the user selects an address from the drop-down, populate the
      	// address fields in the form.
      	autocomplete.addListener('place_changed', fillInAddress);
      }
    } catch (e) {
    	console.log("Error handling autocompete");
    }
  }
}  
</script>

<script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=AIzaSyA-tujnpf8Jy33hVaJ_9GtRdMgHw4jvnwo&libraries=places&callback=initAutocomplete"
        async defer>
</script>
